verseText: Then the king sent and gathered together all the elders of Judah and Jerusalem.
text: NA

verseText: And Jehoshaphat reigned over Judah: he was thirty and five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned twenty and five years in Jerusalem. And his mother’s name was Azubah the daughter of Shilhi.
text: And Jehoshaphat reigned over Judah: he was thirty and five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned twenty and five years in Jerusalem. And his mother’s name was Azubah the daughter of Shilhi.

verseText: But the eye of their God was upon the elders of the Jews, that they could not cause them to cease, till the matter came to Darius: and then they returned answer by letter concerning this matter.

verseText: Then asked we those elders, and said unto them thus, Who commanded you to build this house, and to make up these walls?
text: Then asked we those elders, and said unto them thus, Who commanded you to build this house, and to make up these walls?

text: NA

verseText: Moreover I make a decree what ye shall do to the elders of these Jews for the building of this house of God: that of the king’s goods, even of the tribute beyond the river, forthwith expenses be given unto these men, that they be not hindered.
text: NA

verseText: And the elders of the Jews builded, and they prospered through the prophesying of Haggai the prophet and Zechariah the son of Iddo. And they builded, and finished it, according to the commandment of the God of Israel, and according to the commandment of Cyrus, and Darius, and Artaxerxes king of Persia.
text: NA

verseText: And that whosoever would not come within three days, according to the counsel of the princes and the elders, all his substance should be forfeited, and himself separated from the congregation of those that had been carried away.

verseText: Let now our rulers of all the congregation stand, and let all them which have taken strange wives in our cities come at appointed times, and with them the elders of every city, and the judges thereof, until the fierce wrath of our God for this matter be turned from us.
text: NA

verseText: And the letters were sent by posts into all the king’s provinces, to destroy, to kill, and to cause to perish, all Jews, both young and old, little children and women, in one day, even upon the thirteenth day of the twelfth month, which is the month Adar, and to take the spoil of them for a prey.

verseText: Thou shalt come to thy grave in a full age, like as a shock of corn cometh in in his season.

verseText: With the ancient is wisdom; and in length of days understanding.

verseText: What man is he that desireth life, and loveth many days, that he may see good?

verseText: Cast me not off in the time of old age; forsake me not when my strength faileth.
text: NA

verseText: Now also when I am old and grayheaded, O God, forsake me not; until I have shewed thy strength unto this generation, and thy power to every one that is to come.
text: Now also when I am old and grayheaded, O God, forsake me not; until I have shewed thy strength unto this generation, and thy power to every one that is to come.

verseText: I have considered the days of old, the years of ancient times.
text: NA

verseText: The days of our years are threescore years and ten; and if by reason of strength they be fourscore years, yet is their strength labour and sorrow; for it is soon cut off, and we fly away.

text: He that wasteth his father, and chaseth away his mother, is a son that causeth shame, and bringeth reproach.

verseText: The glory of young men is their strength: and the beauty of old men is the gray head.

verseText: Train up a child in the way he should go: and when he is old, he will not depart from it.

text: NA

verseText: If a man beget an hundred children, and live many years, so that the days of his years be many, and his soul be not filled with good, and also that he have no burial; I say, that an untimely birth is better than he.
text: If a man beget an hundred children, and live many years, so that the days of his years be many, and his soul be not filled with good, and also that he have no burial; I say, that an untimely birth is better than he.

verseText: Yea, though he live a thousand years twice told, yet hath he seen no good: do not all go to one place?
text: Yea, though he live a thousand years twice told, yet hath he seen no good: do not all go to one place?

verseText: Remember now thy Creator in the days of thy youth, while the evil days come not, nor the years draw nigh, when thou shalt say, I have no pleasure in them;

verseText: This is a true saying, If a man desire the office of a bishop, he desireth a good work.
text: NA

verseText: The elder women as mothers; the younger as sisters, with all purity.
text: The elder women as mothers; the younger as sisters, with all purity.

verseText: A bishop then must be blameless, the husband of one wife, vigilant, sober, of good behaviour, given to hospitality, apt to teach;
text: A bishop then must be blameless, the husband of one wife, vigilant, sober, of good behaviour, given to hospitality, apt to teach;

verseText: Honour widows that are widows indeed.
text: Honour widows that are widows indeed.

verseText: Not given to wine, no striker, not greedy of filthy lucre; but patient, not a brawler, not covetous;
text: NA

verseText: But if any widow have children or nephews, let them learn first to shew piety at home, and to requite their parents: for that is good and acceptable before God.
text: But if any widow have children or nephews, let them learn first to shew piety at home, and to requite their parents: for that is good and acceptable before God.
